  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "アクションパズルゲームで、目的はさまざまな色の落ちてくるタイルをキャッチし、同じ色のタイルを縦、横、または斜めに並べることです。各レベルでは異なるパターンを作成する必要があり、ゲームが進むにつれてタイルはより速く、同時に多く落ちてきて、色の数も増えていきます。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Klax is a 1989 computer puzzle game designed by Dave Akers and Mark Stephen Pierce. The object is to line up colored blocks into rows of similar colors to make them disappear, to which the object of Columns is similar. Atari Games originally released it as a coin-op follow up to Tetris, about which they were tangled in a legal dispute at the time.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
